name: vestige_013: CONTAINER prototype A149 - unpowered
description: The prediction of paralogical band, distribution, entropic weighting, decay, and Dead God Pulse strength (PaDEDD) of cryptanomalous entities from their restrained form is a central problem in containment procedure, with great practical importance in [REDACTED]. Creating predictive models conventionally requires substantial trial-and-error for the selection of informational representations, machine learning (ML) algorithms, and hyperparameter tuning. A generally applicable containment method that performs well on all entities without tuning would be of great value but is currently lacking. Here, we present the Co-Ordinated Neutralization Tranquilization And Integration Network Entropy Resonator (CONTAINER), a [REDACTED]-based method for predicting and responding to cryptanomalous [REDACTED]. CONTAINER is a non-parametric, unsupervised containment method developed to generate reliable predictive models and stable containment without need for organic host contribution. CONTAINER's predictive strength is obtained by combining multiple different [REDACTED] in a context-specific manner, while maintaining low dimensionality.
